{{distinguish|Bembe language (Ibembe)|Bemba language}} {{Infobox language |name=Bembe |nativename=''Kibeembe'' |states=[[Republic of Congo]] |speakers={{sigfig|131,0|2}} |date=2007 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone H|Zone H.10]]) |fam6=[[Kongo languages|Kongo]] |dia1=Beembe |dia2=Kamba-Doondo |dia3=Hangala (Ghaangala) |lc1=beq|ld1=Bembe |lc2=xku|ld2=Kamba |lc3=dde|ld3=Doondo |guthrie=H.11,111,112 |glotto=beem1239 |glottoname=Beembe |glotto2=kaam1238 |glottoname2=Kaamba |glotto3=doon1238 |glottoname3=Doondo }}
'''Bembe''' (Kibeembe) is a [[Bantu language]] of [[Congo-Brazzaville]]. It is closely related to [[Kongo language|Kikongo]]. ''Pangwa'' (not the Pangwa of Tanzania) may be a dialect.
Maho (2009) considers Beembe, Kamba-Doondo, and Hangala (Ghaangala) to be distinct languages.
It should not be confused with the [[Bembe language (Ibembe)]] spoken in Congo-Kinshasa and Tanzania.
