{{Infobox World's Fair | box_width = | class = | category = | image = Val-Saint-Lambert JPG001.jpg | image_width = | caption = Monumental vase created for the exposition | year = 1894 | name = | motto = | building = | area = | invent = | visitors = 3000000 | organized = The Count [[Hippolyte d'Ursel]] was Commissioner General and the Count of Pret Roose of Calesburg was President of the Executive Committee | cnt = 23 | org = | biz = | country = [[Belgium]] | city = [[Antwerp]] | venue = | coord = {{coord|51.207389|4.390222|display=inline,title}} | cand = | award = | open = 5 May 1894 | close = 5 November 1894 }}
'''Exposition Internationale d'Anvers''' was a [[World's Fair]] held in [[Antwerp]], Belgium between 5 May and 5 November in 1894. It covered {{convert|65.5|acre|m2}}, attracted 3 million visits and made a profit<ref>{{cite book | editor2-last=Pelle | editor2-first=Kimberley D | editor1-first=John E |editor1-last=Findling | title= Encyclopedia of World's Fairs and Expositions| publisher= McFarland & Company, Inc|location= | isbn=978-0-7864-3416-9 |page=414 }}</ref>
==Participating Nations== <!-- {{flagicon|Germany}} {{flagicon|Austria}} {{flagicon|Bulgaria}} {{flagicon|China}} {{flagicon|Congo}} {{flagicon|Denmark}} {{flagicon|Spain}} {{flagicon|USA}} {{flagicon|United Kingdom|GBI}} {{flagicon|Greece}} {{flagicon|Hungary}} {{flagicon|Italy}} {{flagicon|Luxembourg}} {{flagicon|Mexico}} {{flagicon|Netherlands}} and the Nederland cononies in Asia of Les colonies et possessions Java, Madoura, Sumatra, Bornéo — sauf la partie septentrionale — Banka, Billiton, Célèbes, la plus grande partie de Timor et de la Nouvelle-Guinée, l'archipel des Moluques et de Riouw, etc. flagicon|Persia {{flagicon|Portugal}} {{flagicon|Kingdom of Romania}} {{flagicon|Russia}} {{flagicon|South African Republic|1894}} {{flagicon|SwedenNorway}} {{flagicon|Switzerland}} {{flagicon|Ottoman Empire}} --> There were several participating nations: Germany, Austria, [[Bulgaria]], [[Qing Dynasty|China]], [[Congo Free State|Congo]], Denmark, Spain, United States, [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|United Kingdom]], [[Greece]], Hungary, Italy, [[Luxembourg]], Mexico, [[Iran|Persia]], [[Portugal]], [[Kingdom of Romania]], [[Russian Empire|Russia]], [[South African Republic]], Switzerland and the [[Ottoman Empire]].
There was also a joint presence from Sweden and Norway.
As well as [[Netherlands]] itself there were presentations of the [[Dutch East Indies]] including [[Java]], parts of [[Sumatra]] and [[Madura Island|Madura]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Catalogue officiel général; préliminaires, section Belge, sections spéciales (Volume 2) |edition=1 |volume=2 }} </ref>
==Fair officials== The Count [[Hippolyte d'Ursel]] was the Commissioner General and the Count of Pret Roose of Calesburg the President of the Executive Committee<ref>{{cite book | editor2-last=Pelle | editor2-first=Kimberley D | editor1-first=John E |editor1-last=Findling | title= Encyclopedia of World's Fairs and Expositions| publisher= McFarland & Company, Inc|location= | isbn=978-0-7864-3416-9 |page=419 }}</ref>
==See also== http://www.slv.vic.gov.au/miscpics/0/0/6/doc/mp006678.shtml shows an engraving of the expo grounds.
