{{Unreferenced|date=August 2009}} {{Infobox Radio Station | name = FM Nanami | image = FmNanami.png | area = [[Hiroshima]] / [[Hatsukaichi, Hiroshima|Hatsukaichi]] | branding = ''"JOZZ8AK-FM"'' | slogan = | airdate = April 18, 2004 | frequency = 77.3 ([[Megahertz|MHz]]) | format = [[News radio|News]]/[[Talk radio|Talk]]/[[Music radio|Music]] | erp = 20 [[watt]]s | class = | owner = | website = | callsign_meaning = Itsukaichi Community Broadcast }}
'''Itsukaichi Community Broadcast''' (FM Nanami) was a Japanese community [[FM broadcasting|FM]] radio station in [[Saeki-ku, Hiroshima]].
The station was founded on November 7, 2003 and went on the air on April 18, 2004.
The station stopped broadcasting on December 1, 2007 and closed on March 31, 2008.
