'''Gulu Military Hospital''' is a hospital in [[Gulu]], in the [[Northern Region, Uganda|Northern Region]] of Uganda.<ref name="Mil">{{cite web| url=http://www.urbanafrica.net/news/gulu-clamouring-city-status-after-war/|title=Gulu: Clamouring for City Status After War|last=Odokonyero| date=5 July 2013 |accessdate=26 June 2016 |publisher=UrbanAfrica.Net| first=Moses |location=Cape Town}}</ref>
==Location== It is located in the city of [[Gulu]], in [[Gulu District]], in the [[Acholi sub-region]], in Northern Uganda, on the campus of the headquarters of the 4th Division of the [[Uganda People's Defence Force]] (UPDF), about {{convert|3|km|0}} northwest of [[Gulu Regional Referral Hospital]].<ref>{{cite web| accessdate=26 June 2016 | publisher=Globefeed.com | url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Uganda_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Kasubi%20Central%20Primary%20School%2C%20Gulu%2C%20Northern%20Region%2C%20Uganda&toplace=Gulu%20Hospital%2C%20Gulu%2C%20Northern%20Region%2C%20Uganda%2C&dt1=ChIJDxhHDGKmcRcR4OvfD8Hu2AI&dt2=ChIJe325kEWmcRcRq1tzdZyvnaw| date=26 June 2016 |author=Globefeed.com |title=Distance between Kasubi Central Primary School, Gulu, Northern Region, Uganda and Gulu Regional Referral Hospital, Gulu, Northern Region, Uganda}}</ref> The hospital caters to UPDF personnel and their families.<ref name="Mil"/><ref>{{cite web|newspaper=[[Daily Monitor]] |location=Kampala|accessdate=26 June 2016| url=http://www.monitor.co.ug/News/National/Police-officer-shot-Gulu-attacks-dies-hospital/-/688334/3248912/-/89lyho/-/index.html|title=Police officer shot in Gulu attack succumbs to injuries |date=14 June 2016 |author=Monitor Reporter}}</ref>
