'''Hong Kong Volunteer Company''' ({{zh|'''香港志願連'''}}) was a company that served in India and Burma during the [[Burma Campaign]] in [[World War II]]. Following the [[Japanese occupation of Hong Kong|Hong Kong surrender]], a number of British-Chinese soldiers made their escape to China and volunteered to go to India to join the British Army and fight the Japanese. They were originally attached to the [[Chindits]] Force and later deployed to [[Japanese occupation of Malaya|Japanese-occupied Malaya]] conducting special reconnaissance behind enemy lines.

