{{unreferenced|date=November 2013}} {{Infobox radio station | name = Malacca FM | image = Malacca FM Logo.png | city = [[Kuala Lumpur]] | area = [[West Malaysia]] | branding = | slogan = | frequency = Varies depending on its region | translator = | repeater = | airdate = {{start date and age|2002|df=yes}} | last airdate = <!-- for defunct stations --> | share = | share as of = | share source = | format = [[Talk radio|Talk]], [[contemporary hit radio]] | language = [[Malay language|Malay]] | power = | erp = | haat = | class = | facility_id = | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|}} --> | callsign_meaning = | former_callsigns = | former_frequencies = <!-- use – --> | affiliations = | owner = [[Radio Televisyen Malaysia]] | licensee = | sister_stations = [[Asyik FM]], Bintulu FM, [[Johor FM]], IKIM.fm, Kedah FM, Kelantan FM, Keningau FM, [[KL FM]], Labuan FM, Langkawi FM, Limbang FM, Miri FM, [[Mutiara FM]], [[Negeri FM]], [[Pahang FM]], Perak FM, Perlis FM, RaSa FM, Red FM, Sabah FM, Sabah Vfm, Sandakan FM, [[Sarawak FM]], [[Selangor FM]], Sibu FM, Tawau FM, Terengganu FM, UFM and Wai FM | webcast = | website = {{URL|http://melakafm.rtm.gov.my/}} }}
'''Malacca FM''' is a regional [[Malay language]] [[radio station]] operated by [[Radio Televisyen Malaysia]] out of the state capital of [[Malacca]], [[Malaysia]]. Transmissions started in 1946 from the [[Stadthuys]] building. Broadcasts are daily in [[Malay language|Malay]] from 06:00 to 00:00 featuring local [[news]] and [[Malaysian music]]. It transmits on [[frequency modulation|FM]] 102.3&nbsp;MHz from Gunung Ledang. The Melaka FM transmissions were formerly on [[amplitude modulation|AM]] 1008&nbsp;kHz, until 2002. It can be received statewide as well as in some parts of [[Johor]], [[Negeri Sembilan]] and south west [[Pahang]] (Bandar Tun Abdul Razak and Bandar Muadzam Shah).
== Etymology == The station was formerly known as Radio Malaysia Melaka and Radio 3 Melaka.
