{{unreferenced|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox Icelandic court |court_name = National High Court |native_name = Landsyfirréttur |established = 1800 |dissolved = 1920 |country = [[Iceland]] |location = [[Reykjavík]] |coordinates = |type = [[High court]] |composition = |authority = |appeal = [[Supreme Court of Denmark]] |term = |positions = |budget = }} {{Politics of Iceland}} The '''National High Court''' ({{Lang-is|Landsyfirréttur í Reykjavík}}, {{Lang-da|Landsoverretten i Reykjavik}}) was a [[high court]] in [[Iceland]] established in 1800. The court was established due to dissatisfaction with the [[High Court (Iceland)|High Court]] which had been the high court of the country from 1563. In 1920, the [[Supreme Court of Iceland]] was established replacing the National High Court.
